                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-defend2749" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t18270913-392-defend2750" type="defendantName">
                  JAMES 
                  JACKSON
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-defend2750" type="surname" value="JACKSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-defend2750" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-defend2750" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-defend2750" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were indicted for <rs id="t18270913-392-off2161" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-off2161" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-off2161" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270913-392-cd2162" type="crimeDate">14th of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-392-off2161 t18270913-392-cd2162"></join>, 2 table-spoons, value 3s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18270913-392-victim2751" type="victimName">
                  Joseph 
                  Quarterman
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-victim2751" type="surname" value="Quarterman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-victim2751" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-victim2751" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-392-off2161 t18270913-392-victim2751"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-392-person2752">
                  SARAH 
                  PIPER
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2752" type="surname" value="PIPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2752" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2752" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Joseph Quarterman. On the 14th of September, the prisoners came at half-past five o'clock in the morning to sweep the chimneys - I had seen these spoons in the kitchen closet the night before; it was not locked - I missed them soon after the prisoners were gone; nobody else had been in the house - they were not above ten minutes in the house - I gave information; they were apprehended that morning - Hardy had called the day before, to know if we wanted the sweeps; he said they came from Mr. Donald, and I told him to come.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-392-person2753">
                  GEORGE 
                  CULL
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2753" type="surname" value="CULL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2753" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2753" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am beadle of St. Mary-le-bone. About ten minutes past six o'clock in the morning I was informed of this robbery - I apprehended the two prisoners immediately; one Brown gave me information - I found these spoons in Jackson's hosom; he owned be had taken them; he had said he had nothing about him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-392-person2754">
                  JOHN 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2754" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2754" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2754" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a chimney-sweeper. About a quarter-past five o'clock my boy gave me information - I went to the prosecutor's, and waited: the prisoners came out - I took hold of Harding, and gave them in charge, on suspicion, and saw the spoons found on Jackson; they were never in my employ; they work for Donald.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-392-person2755">
                  CHARLES 
                  TALBOT
               <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2755" type="surname" value="TALBOT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2755" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-person2755" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a chimney-sweeper. At half-past five o'clock in the morning I was told the prisoners were gone to No. 8, Quebec-street to sweep chimneys - we waited them out, and secured them.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>HARDING'S Defence. I did not know he had them.</p>
               <p>SARAH PIPER. Jackson went up the chimney.</p>
               <p>HARDING - <rs id="t18270913-392-verdict2163" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-392-verdict2163" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
